s assigned to the board. Simply copy that IP address… then open the transmitter code and paste it in the correct place. Once that’s done, go ahead and upload the transmitter code as well. And from this point onward, everything works exactly the same way. The transmitter keeps sending the temperature value over your local network, and the ESP32-S3 on the receiver side prints that value onto the E-Ink display — clear, sharp, and paper-like, just the way E-Ink is meant to be. It’s fast, reliable, and honestly pretty fun to watch because the entire system feels like a proper real-world wireless monitoring setup. So, that’s all for now. Watch Video Tutorial: Discover more from Electronic Clinic Subscribe to get the latest posts sent to your email. Type your email… Subscribe Engr. Shahzada Fahad 225 Share Facebook X LinkedIn Pinterest Reddit Skype Messenger Messenger WhatsApp Line Share via Email Print
